terrestrial or aquatic ecosystems in seasonally snow-covered watersheds. In these systems, changes in surface water chemistry are likely to occur in high deposition, snow-covered sites during low snow years before terrestrial vegetation is affected. Copyright {\textcopyright} 1999 John Wiley {\&} Sons, Ltd.},
